setting.name: Setting
setting.gameTooltip:
Select which game calculator to use,
or use the links in the title bar.
setting.modSetTooltip: Select which version or set of mods in Factorio to use.
setting.modVersionsTooltip: Versions of game/mods in this data set
setting.disabledTooltip:
Click to modify which recipes are disabled.
Disabled recipes will not be used in the solution.
setting.difficultyTooltip:
Select whether to use Normal or
Expensive difficulty recipes.
setting.columnsAndPrecisionTooltip:
Click to select the visible columns and decimal
or fractional precision for visible columns.
setting.saveStatesTooltip:
Click edit to name and save the current calculator state.
Select a saved state from the dropdown to load it into the calculator.
setting.displayRateTooltip: Set the unit of time to use in rates.
setting.powerUnitTooltip: Set the unit of power to use in the power column.
setting.presetTooltip: Select a default preset of factory settings to use.
setting.estimateBeaconPowerUsageTooltip:
Enable to estimate power usage of beacons as well as factories.
Requires an estimated average number of receivers per beacon.
setting.averageBeaconReceiversTooltip:
The average number of factories affected by each beacon.
Minimum possible value is 1.
setting.proliferatorSelfSprayTooltip: Select the proliferator spray applied to proliferator itself.
setting.defaultTransportBeltTooltip: Select the default belt to be used by all items.
setting.defaultPipeTooltip: Select the default pipe to be used by all fluids.
setting.defaultCargoWagonTooltip: Select the default cargo wagon to be used by all items.
setting.defaultFluidWagonTooltip: Select the default fluid wagon to be used by all fluids.
setting.chemicalFuelTooltip:
Select the default chemical to be used where applicable.
This does not affect burners that use non-chemical fuels.
setting.miningProductivityTooltip:
Enter the current mining productivity bonus percent.
Default is 0%.
setting.miningSpeedTooltip:
Enter the current mining speed with bonus.
Default is 100%.
setting.researchSpeedTooltip:
Enter the current level of research speed bonus.
This setting only affects research products.
setting.inserterCapacityTooltip:
Enter the current level of inserter capacity bonus.
This setting only affects inserter estimates.
setting.simplexSolverTooltip:
Select to enable/disable the simplex solver.
Disable simplex to more easily modify settings
when simplex is slow and causes lag.
setting.simplexSolverTitle: Disable to get a faster but incomplete result
setting.simplexSolverInvalid:
Disabling simplex improves performance but usually results in an
incomplete solution.

ranker.rankerModuleInfo: (Optional) Select another module to use as a fallback
ranker.rankerProliferatorInfo: (Optional) Select another proliferator to use as a fallback

list.clickToOpenThisStepInANewTab: Click to open this step in a new tab
list.insertCalculateRemark:

list.defaultRecipeInfo1:
Click to set a recipe as the default for this item. If set,
the default recipe is treated as the only way to produce this
item.
list.defaultRecipeInfo2: The recipe must be enabled and must only produce this item.
list.defaultRecipeInfo3: Default was ignored due to a detected circular loop.
list.enabledRecipesInfo:
Click recipes to enable or disable them. Disabled recipes will
not be used in the solution.
list.selectANodeToSeeDetails: Select a node to see details
list.requiredRecipesInfo: Recipes that produce this item but cannot be disabled because they are required to produce another item.
